    <string name="about_project_heading">Why this app?</string>
    <string name="about_project_text1">The water temperature is a value relevant to a lot of people: Swimmers, divers, fishermen, and many others. But until now, in Switzerland, there were often no reliable ways to get real time information about the water temperature in the area you\'re interested in.</string>
    <string name="about_project_text2">We are building a network of low-cost low-energy water temperature sensors. This allows us to measure the water temperature locally and to show it to you in real time, for free.</string>
    <string name="about_project_text3">Find more information about this project: https://gfrör.li/</string>
    <string name="about_us_heading">Who made this app?</string>
    <string name="about_us_text1">This app, the server infrastructure as well as the water temperature sensor hardware is developed by the Coredump hackerspace in Rapperswil-Jona.</string>
    <string name="about_us_text2">Find more information about us on our website: https://www.coredump.ch/</string>
    <string name="open_source_heading">Open Source</string>
    <string name="open_source_text1">This app is open source! You can find the code on GitHub: https://github.com/gfroerli/app-android</string>

